Summary: Port to the Mac OS
Class: wish
Priority: medium
Difficulty: tricky
Depends: remove-statics
Content-type: text/x-html-body

<p>
There are ports to classic Mac OS and Mac OS X in progress. They're both
at the just-about-usable stage, but are a long way from release, and
things might behave unexpectedly and change without warning. See:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.tartarus.org/~simon-anonsvn/viewcvs.cgi/putty/mac/README.mac?view=markup">mac/README.mac</a> (classic Mac OS)
<li><a href="http://www.tartarus.org/~simon-anonsvn/viewcvs.cgi/putty/macosx/README.OSX?view=markup">macosx/README.OSX</a> (Mac OS X native)
<li>the <a href="../faq.html#QA.3.6">FAQ entry</a>
</ul>
